# Adaptive Monte Carlo + BehaviorSpace Integration (NetLogo Implementation Spec)

## 🎯 Objective

Implement a NetLogo experiment architecture that:

1. Runs **adaptive Monte Carlo simulations** internally
2. Stops automatically when **statistical significance is reached**
3. Integrates with **BehaviorSpace** for parameter sweeps and CSV export

---

## 🧠 Core Concept

Each BehaviorSpace run will:

* Execute **multiple internal simulations**
* Dynamically estimate:

  * Win probability (p̂)
  * Margin of error (MOE)
  * Standard deviation (σ)
* Stop when:

  * MOE < target threshold (e.g., 0.05 for ±5%)

---

## 🏗️ REQUIRED MODEL ARCHITECTURE

---

## 1. GLOBAL VARIABLES

Add the following globals:

```netlogo
globals [
  ;; experiment tracking
  runs
  british-wins
  durations

  ;; statistics
  p-hat
  moe
  std-duration

  ;; parameters
  target-moe
  z-score
  max-runs
]
```

---

## 2. REQUIRED REPORTERS (CRITICAL)

These must exist for each simulation run:

```netlogo
to-report british-win?
  report any? british-troops and not any? argentine-troops
end

to-report conflict-duration
  report ticks
end
```

---

## 3. STOP CONDITION FOR A SINGLE SIMULATION

```netlogo
to-report simulation-over?
  report (not any? argentine-troops) or (not any? british-troops)
end
```

---

## 4. GO PROCEDURE (MODIFIED)

⚠️ IMPORTANT: `go` now runs the ENTIRE adaptive experiment

```netlogo
to go
  run-until-converged
  stop
end
```

---

## 5. FULL SETUP (FOR BEHAVIORSPACE)

This runs once per BehaviorSpace experiment:

```netlogo
to setup
  clear-all
  reset-ticks

  ;; initialize global parameters
  set target-moe 0.05      ;; desired ±5% confidence
  set z-score 1.96         ;; 95% confidence interval
  set max-runs 1000        ;; safety cap

  ;; initialize any scenario parameters
  ;; (carrier distance, NGFS toggles, etc.)
end
```

---

## 6. SIMULATION SETUP (VERY IMPORTANT)

⚠️ DO NOT USE clear-all here

This resets ONLY per-simulation state:

```netlogo
to setup-simulation
  clear-turtles
  reset-ticks

  ;; reinitialize troop positions, morale, etc.
  ;; DO NOT reset global experiment variables
end
```

---

## 7. MAIN ADAPTIVE CONTROLLER

```netlogo
to run-until-converged

  ;; reset experiment state
  set runs 0
  set british-wins 0
  set durations []
  set p-hat 0
  set moe 1
  set std-duration 0

  while [true] [

    ;; run one simulation
    setup-simulation
    go-until-end

    ;; record outcome
    if british-win? [
      set british-wins british-wins + 1
    ]

    set durations lput conflict-duration durations
    set runs runs + 1

    ;; update statistics
    update-stats

    ;; optional debug output
    print (word "Run: " runs
                " | p: " precision p-hat 3
                " | MOE: " precision moe 4)

    ;; stopping condition
    if (runs > 30) and (moe < target-moe) [
      stop
    ]

    ;; safety stop
    if runs >= max-runs [
      print "Max runs reached without convergence"
      stop
    ]
  ]
end
```

---

## 8. RUN-UNTIL-END PROCEDURE

```netlogo
to go-until-end
  while [not simulation-over?] [
    go-step
  ]
end
```

---

## 9. SINGLE STEP LOGIC (RENAME YOUR CURRENT go)

⚠️ IMPORTANT: rename your existing `go` logic to `go-step`

```netlogo
to go-step
  ;; ALL EXISTING MODEL LOGIC GOES HERE

  ;; troop movement
  ;; combat
  ;; NGFS
  ;; terrain effects

  tick
end
```

---

## 10. STATISTICS UPDATE FUNCTION

```netlogo
to update-stats

  set p-hat british-wins / runs

  ;; margin of error for proportion
  set moe z-score * sqrt((p-hat * (1 - p-hat)) / runs)

  ;; duration standard deviation
  if length durations > 1 [
    set std-duration standard-deviation durations
  ]
end
```

---

## 11. FINAL REPORTERS FOR BEHAVIORSPACE

These are what BehaviorSpace will export:

```netlogo
to-report final-p
  report p-hat
end

to-report final-duration-mean
  report mean durations
end

to-report final-duration-std
  report std-duration
end

to-report final-runs-used
  report runs
end

to-report final-moe
  report moe
end
```

