## ⚠️ CRITICAL REQUIREMENTS

---

### 1. NEVER call `setup` inside loop

Use `setup-simulation`

---

### 2. ALWAYS include:

```
if runs > 30
```

Prevents early instability

---

### 3. ALWAYS include max-runs safety cap

---

### 4. ENSURE:

* Each simulation is independent
* No state leaks between runs

---

### 5. RANDOMNESS

Ensure each simulation varies:

```netlogo
random-seed new-seed
```

(or allow NetLogo default randomness)

---

## 🚀 EXTENSIONS (OPTIONAL)

---

### Add duration convergence:

```netlogo
let duration-moe z-score * (std-duration / sqrt(runs))

if (moe < target-moe) and (duration-moe < duration-threshold) [
  stop
]
```

---

### Add CSV export (manual alternative)

```netlogo
file-open "results.csv"
file-print (word runs "," p-hat "," moe)
file-close
```

